The DCI on Monday recovered Team Kenya Nike uniforms after raiding the house of deputy Chef-de-Mission for Rio 2016 Olympics, Ben Ekumbo.Boxes containing shoes track suits and bags were recovered from Ekumbo's house at Duplex apartments along professor Saitoti Avenue in Nairobi's Westlands.Police said the raid was part of the their investigations into the Rio games scandal.Ekumbo was questioned in his house during the afternoon operation as officers loaded the kits, including running and swimming gear, into their vehicle.Read: Kenyan officials "embezzled money meant for Rio team" - State reportIn September, a Team Kenya athletics official was linked with the disappearance of assorted kits meant to be used by the country s Olympic team in Rio.Kithinji Maragara was arraigned before senior principal magistrate Charity Oluoch and was charged with theft. He was accused of stealing an assortment of kits on July 29 within Nairobi county.Also read: Team Kenya official charged with theft of Rio Olympics kit